            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1945-10-11T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1945-10-11T00:00:00-05:00" n="893" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d893">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">861.8623/10–1145</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Embassy of the Soviet Union</gloss> to
                        the <gloss type="to">Department of State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Translation]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>The Embassy of the Union of Soviet Socialist Republics presents its compliments
                    to the Department of State and, referring to the Department’s note of October 2,
                    1945, has the honor to communicate that, in view of the lack of cooperation on
                    the part of the Department of State, a decision has not been reached on the
                    question of the transfer <pb facs="1160" n="1148" xml:id="pg_1148"/> by the
                    American authorities to the Soviet authorities of seamen Pik and Lobanov, who
                    deserted in time of war.</p>
                <closer>
                    <dateline rendition="#left">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-10-11">October 11,
                            1945</date>.</dateline>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
